The standard room was very good, on the ground floor overlooking the patio area, and we would have happily stayed there if the king suite had been unavailable.	I recommend room 326… vaulted ceiling with cedar beams, king bed, wet bar and a fantastic water view… at a standard room price.	We had to change our itinerary beforehand, so could only have a standard room for the first night and then a king suite for the following 2 nights.	The standard room was a good size, clean and attractive.	The overall standard is good especially cleanliness and service.	The room was very spacious with a lovely king size bed and nice toiletries, replenished daily.